SIMPLE: ostentatious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ostentatious
<hw>Os`ten*ta"tious</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Fond of, or
evincing, ostentation; unduly conspicuous; pretentious;
boastful.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Far from being <qex>ostentatious</qex> of the good you do.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>ostentatious</qex> professions of many years.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Os`ten*ta"tious*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Os`ten*ta"tious*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ostentator</ent>⟦br⟧
